    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Add the <strong>potato discs</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and sprinkle them with<strong> cold water </strong>(this will help the potatoes cook through!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-indian-style-spiced-tomato-and-potato-gratin/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are in the oven, peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to caramelise</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-indian-style-spiced-tomato-and-potato-gratin/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic </strong>and chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Once the onion has slightly caramelised, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped cherry tomatoes</strong> and your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the garlic has softened, then transfer to a plate and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli tomato mixture</strong></p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-indian-style-spiced-tomato-and-potato-gratin/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mixture is cooking, slice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Preheat the grill to very high</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-indian-style-spiced-tomato-and-potato-gratin/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat and once hot, add your <strong>ground coriander </strong>and <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>creamy single soy </strong>gradually to the roux with your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>spiced cream</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-indian-style-spiced-tomato-and-potato-gratin/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have softened, layer the <strong>sliced potatoes</strong> and the <strong>chilli tomato mixture</strong> in an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Pour the <strong>spiced cream</strong> all over and top with the <strong>tomato rounds</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and put the dish under the grill for 8-10 min or until bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>plant-based</strong> <strong>Indian-style spiced tomato & potato gratin</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-indian-style-spiced-tomato-and-potato-gratin/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the gratin is in the oven, dice your <strong>cucumber</strong></p><p>Bash your <strong>cashews </strong>roughly with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>diced cucumber</strong>, <strong>bashed cashews</strong> and <strong>black sesame seeds </strong>in a bowl with the juice from your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s] </strong>and a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>nutty cucumber salad</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-indian-style-spiced-tomato-and-potato-gratin/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>plant-based</strong> <strong>Indian-style spiced tomato & potato gratin </strong>with the<strong> nutty cucumber salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
